lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Hong Kong leader Carrie Lam says the plan that ignited the revolt in her city was born of a straightforward quest for justice.
headline_main: Special Report: How Murder, Kidnappings and Miscalculation Set Off Hong Kong's Revolt

abstract: St. Lucia buns, smothered shrimp, pots de crème: Celebrate the longest night of the year with the food that comforts you.
snippet: St. Lucia buns, smothered shrimp, pots de crème: Celebrate the longest night of the year with the food that comforts you.
lead_paragraph: Good morning. It’s the longest night of the year this weekend, Saturday night, the hibernal solstice, a chance to light candles, make and eat St. Lucia buns, smothered shrimp in crab-meat gravy, okonomi-latkes piled high with salmon roe. I think maybe I’d like to make chicken Francese (above), this year’s most popular recipe on NYT Cooking, and pair it with spaghetti tossed with a little olive oil and a lot of Parmesan, some garlic bread on the side.

abstract: Protesters are speaking out against what they say is a government bent on attacking diversity, the foundation on which India was built.
snippet: Protesters are speaking out against what they say is a government bent on attacking diversity, the foundation on which India was built.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Wearing Muslim skullcaps, colorful turbans of Indian Sikhs or hip beanies of secular university students, thousands protested at the largest mosque in India’s capital on Friday, a turbulent scene that played out in multiple cities across the country. They defied government curfews, internet shutdowns and the divisive politics that have kept them apart for years.

abstract: Giannis Antetokounmpo vs. LeBron James, young vs. old, was billed as a pass-the-baton moment. But don’t read too much into one game.
snippet: Giannis Antetokounmpo vs. LeBron James, young vs. old, was billed as a pass-the-baton moment. But don’t read too much into one game.
lead_paragraph: MILWAUKEE — Early in the fourth quarter, the Los Angeles Lakers, those gold-and-purple princes with their lordly leader LeBron James, awakened from a slumber and were pressing the Milwaukee Bucks, cutting a once mountainous lead to single digits.

abstract: Shareholders of Yandex, Russia's biggest technology company, approved changes to its corporate governance on Friday to allow a "golden share" to be held by a new entity, to assuage Kremlin fears about potential foreign influence.
snippet: Shareholders of Yandex, Russia's biggest technology company, approved changes to its corporate governance on Friday to allow a "golden share" to be held by a new entity, to assuage Kremlin fears about potential foreign influence.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Shareholders of Yandex, Russia's biggest technology company, approved changes to its corporate governance on Friday to allow a "golden share" to be held by a new entity, to assuage Kremlin fears about potential foreign influence.
headline_main: Yandex Shareholders Approve Governance Changes to Allay Kremlin Fears
headline_print_headline: Yandex Shareholders Approve Governance Changes to Allay Kremlin Fears

abstract: Iraq's top Shiite cleric called Friday for the speedy formation of a government and early elections as ongoing political wrangling caused Parliament to miss a deadline to name the next premier. That has sparked concerns of protracted political crisis and uncertainty.
snippet: Iraq's top Shiite cleric called Friday for the speedy formation of a government and early elections as ongoing political wrangling caused Parliament to miss a deadline to name the next premier. That has sparked concerns of protracted political cri...
lead_paragraph: BAGHDAD — Iraq's top Shiite cleric called Friday for the speedy formation of a government and early elections as ongoing political wrangling caused Parliament to miss a deadline to name the next premier. That has sparked concerns of protracted political crisis and uncertainty.
headline_main: Iraq's Top Cleric Calls for Quick Formation of Government
headline_print_headline: Iraq's Top Cleric Calls for Quick Formation of Government

abstract: Officers who mistakenly entered a home trying to arrest an Alabama man who was already in jail shot a woman who was inside, news outlets reported.
snippet: Officers who mistakenly entered a home trying to arrest an Alabama man who was already in jail shot a woman who was inside, news outlets reported.
lead_paragraph: MOBILE, Ala. — Officers who mistakenly entered a home trying to arrest an Alabama man who was already in jail shot a woman who was inside, news outlets reported.
headline_main: Officers Shoot Woman During Search for Man Already in Jail
headline_print_headline: Officers Shoot Woman During Search for Man Already in Jail

abstract: A South African telecoms company backed by investment firm Remgro plans to expand its high-speed broadband network after completing a 16 billion rand ($1 billion) debt restructuring this week.
